{
  "text": "Tioman virus (TiV) was isolated from the urine of a fruit bat (P. hypomelanus) during a search for Nipah virus on an island off the eastern coast of peninsular Malaysia [CITATION_1] . The only serological relationship between TiV and other known paramyxoviruses is with Menangle virus found in Australia. The pathogenesis of TiV in other mammalian species is unknown.",
  "correct_citation": {
